Hi All,

RE: Tender Review - C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport [WW-ACTIV=
E.FID3167762] [WYNNW-ACTIVE.FID3167762]

Find below and attached the current response from Tower Insurance regarding=
 the determinations of claim # C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport
For the purposes of this response, we initially address the concerns articu=
lated in paragraph 3 of the Wynn Williams letter (the concerns). These conc=
erns which center around the proposed scope of works being applied under Sc=
hedule 1 of the building Act 2004. These concerns are expressly addressed i=
n the PDF attachment: ANZ1789 Response to building consent concerns & 39775=
 23 Mays Street, Devonport Post Fire Structural Assessment REV B , May 26


Further to the issue addressed above regarding the application of Schedule =
1, we have been notified of other concerns noted within the Prendos report.=
 I have provided Tower Insurances response to those below, using the clause=
 heading referencing of the Prendos report where possible. Obviously, many =
points below are also addressed in the 2 reports provided as attached. Plea=
se excuse the duplication. As follows:


6.2.1 =E2=80=93 Three braced walls.

Please refer to =E2=80=98ANZ1789 Response to building consent concerns=E2=
=80=99 [Attached]


6.2.2 =E2=80=93 Load bearing walls, braced walls, and floor joists

Isolated components of load-bearing walls are identified as being charred a=
s referred to in section 5.10 & 5.11 of the ASURNZ material damage report d=
ated 4 September 2025, and the post fire structural assessment provide by K=
CL.

ASURNZ damage report:
[5.10] =E2=80=93 Charring has occurred to the timber wall framing of the ba=
sement hallway above the door openings of the storage room, and above the d=
oor opening to the kitchenette.
[5.11] =E2=80=93 The underside of the hardwood flooring of bedroom 2 and se=
veral midfloor joist are charred.

KCL Report: Structural Repairs
The charred joists and strip flooring above the kitchenette and bathroom ar=
ea will require replacement along with the charred internal load bearing wa=
ll supporting the joists over the bathroom. This amounts to three charred j=
oists and the associated blocking and flooring above, and the load bearing =
timber framed wall supporting these joists.

Tower Insurance and its expert consultants have identified all the same ind=
ividual damaged components referred to in the Prendos report. Our response =
to the repair and replacement of those components was provided to all parti=
es in Section 9.0 the ASURNZ Material Damage Report dated 4 September 2025.=
 I will provide again below for your reference:

9.0 Building Consent and Design Requirements
The proposed repair work involves the replacement of existing building prod=
ucts with comparable building products in the same position, including the =
repair/replacement of internal timber wall framing and several floor joists=
 (not a complete or substantial replacement of a wall/floor framing assembl=
y), the replacement of wall, floor and ceiling linings, and the replacement=
 of plumbing fittings and fixtures. This is building work that is described=
 in Section 1, Section 12, or Section 32 of Schedule 1 of the Building Act =
2004 (the Act), thereby satisfying the provisions of Section 42A of the Act=
 as building work that does not require a building consent. Note that altho=
ugh a building consent is not required, the building work being undertaken =
must comply with the building code to the extent required by the Act. In th=
is regard, the provisions of Section 42A (2) of the Act apply for the repai=
r of the existing building, in that after the building work is complete, th=
e building must continue to comply with the building code to at least the s=
ame extent as it did immediately before the damage from the event occurred.=
 In effect this means that there is no requirement to upgrade parts of the =
building that are incidental to or not included in the building work.

Please refer further to =E2=80=98ANZ1789 Response to building consent conce=
rns=E2=80=99 & 39775 23 Mays Street, Devonport Post Fire Structural Assessm=
ent REV B , May 26 [Attached]


