<body lang=3D"EN-US" link=3D"blue" vlink=3D"purple" style=3D"word-wrap:brea=
k-word">
<div class=3D"WordSection1">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hi All,<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">RE: Tender Revie=
w - C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport [WW-ACTIVE.FID3167762] [W=
YNNW-ACTIVE.FID3167762]<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Find below and atta=
ched the current response from Tower Insurance regarding the determinations=
 of claim # C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">For the purposes of=
 this response, we initially address the concerns articulated in paragraph =
3 of the Wynn Williams letter (the concerns). These concerns which center a=
round the proposed scope of works being
 applied under Schedule 1 of the building Act 2004. These concerns are expr=
essly addressed in the PDF attachment:
<b><i><u>ANZ1789 Response to building consent concerns</u></i></b><i> &amp;=
 <b><u>39775 23 Mays Street, Devonport Post Fire Structural Assessment REV =
B , May 26</u></b>
</i>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Further to the issu=
e addressed above regarding the application of Schedule 1, we have been not=
ified of other concerns noted within the Prendos report. I have provided To=
wer Insurances response to those below,
 using the clause heading referencing of the Prendos report where possible.=
 Obviously, many points below are also addressed in the 2 reports provided =
as attached. Please excuse the duplication. As follows: &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-la=
nguage:EN-US">6.2.1 =E2=80=93 Three braced walls.</span></u><u><span lang=
=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,=
sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></u>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-langu=
age:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Ple=
ase refer to =E2=80=98</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&q=
uot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif">ANZ1789 Response to building consent
 concerns=E2=80=99 [Attached] <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">&nbs=
p;&nbsp;<span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-langu=
age:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-la=
nguage:EN-US">6.2.2 =E2=80=93 Load bearing walls, braced walls, and floor j=
oists<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-langu=
age:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Iso=
lated components of load-bearing walls are identified as being charred as r=
eferred to in section 5.10 &amp; 5.11 of the ASURNZ
 material damage report dated 4 September 2025, and the post fire structura=
l assessment provide by KCL.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
<o:p><span style=3D"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
ASURNZ damage report:
<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">[5.=
10] =E2=80=93 Charring has occurred to the timber wall framing of the basem=
ent hallway above the door openings of the storage room,
 and above the door opening to the kitchenette.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">[5.=
11] =E2=80=93 The underside of the hardwood flooring of bedroom 2 and sever=
al midfloor joist are charred.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p><span styl=
e=3D"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">KCL Report: Str=
uctural Repairs<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The charred joists=
 and strip flooring above the kitchenette and bathroom area will require re=
placement along with the charred internal load
 bearing wall supporting the joists over the bathroom. This amounts to thre=
e charred joists and the associated blocking and flooring above, and the lo=
ad bearing timber framed wall supporting these joists.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Tower Insurance an=
d its expert consultants have identified all the same individual damaged co=
mponents referred to in the Prendos report. Our
 response to the repair and replacement of those components was provided to=
 all parties in Section 9.0 the ASURNZ Material Damage Report dated 4 Septe=
mber 2025. I will provide again below for your reference:<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">9.0 Building Co=
nsent and Design Requirements<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The proposed repai=
r work involves the replacement of existing building products with comparab=
le building products in the same position, including
 the repair/replacement of internal timber wall framing and several floor j=
oists (not a complete or substantial replacement of a wall/floor framing as=
sembly), the replacement of wall, floor and ceiling linings, and the replac=
ement of plumbing fittings and fixtures.
 This is building work that is described in Section 1, Section 12, or Secti=
on 32 of Schedule 1 of the Building Act 2004 (the Act), thereby satisfying =
the provisions of Section 42A of the Act as building work that does not req=
uire a building consent. Note that
 although a building consent is not required, the building work being under=
taken must comply with the building code to the extent required by the Act.=
 In this regard, the provisions of Section 42A (2) of the Act apply for the=
 repair of the existing building,
 in that after the building work is complete, the building must continue to=
 comply with the building code to at least the same extent as it did immedi=
ately before the damage from the event occurred. In effect this means that =
there is no requirement to upgrade
 parts of the building that are incidental to or not included in the buildi=
ng work.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p=
>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
