<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Rel=
ates to recurring point of contention regarding the correct application of =
Schedule 1 of the Building Act, 2004. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Ple=
ase refer to =E2=80=98</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&q=
uot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif">ANZ1789 Response to building consent
 concerns=E2=80=99 [Attached] <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&q=
uot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US=
"><o:p><span style=3D"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u><=
/b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-la=
nguage:EN-US">7.3.3<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-la=
nguage:EN-US"><o:p><span style=3D"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p>=
</span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Ref=
er to response provided in letter to Wyn Williams dated 27 March, 2026. As =
follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:=
p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Policy Standard
<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">11. The applicable=
 standard for reinstatement is governed by the express terms of the Policy.=
 It is not determined by trade terminology used
 in a scope of works, nor by subjective expectations as to aesthetic outcom=
e. <o:p>
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">12. Under the Poli=
cy, Tower=E2=80=99s obligation in the event of an economic repair is to mee=
t the reasonable cost of repairing the house to a standard
 that is reasonably equivalent to its appearance, size, functionality, and =
relative quality when new, without necessarily reproducing it exactly. That=
 formulation reflects a well-established distinction in New Zealand insuran=
ce law between a requirement to
 restore functional and qualitative equivalence, and any obligation to deli=
ver a pristine or upgraded outcome.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">13. Where damage i=
s repaired rather than replaced in full, the Policy recognises that the rep=
aired element cannot, in a literal sense, be rendered
 =E2=80=9Cnew=E2=80=9D. In those circumstances, the applicable standard is =
directed to the materials and workmanship used in the repair, assessed by r=
eference to whether the completed works restore the relevant element to a c=
ondition that is reasonably equivalent in function
 and quality to its insured state, rather than whether the element is indis=
tinguishable from a newly constructed component.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">14. The Policy doe=
s not impose an obligation to improve, upgrade, or replicate owner-driven r=
enovations, nor does it require reinstatement
 to current building standards except to the extent required by law. The us=
e of modern materials and methods is contemplated only as a means of achiev=
ing the required functional equivalence, not as a basis for elevating the s=
tandard of the building beyond that
 insured. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">15. The scope prep=
ared by Asurnz was developed to give effect to this contractual standard. I=
t reflects the assessor=E2=80=99s determination of what
 work is reasonably required to repair the insured damage, including replac=
ement where necessary and cleaning, repainting, or reinstatement where repl=
acement is not required. The absence of the phrase =E2=80=9Cwhen new=E2=80=
=9D in the scope does not alter the standard to be
 applied, which is fixed by the Policy wording itself. <o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">16. Any assessment=
 of the adequacy of the scope or of completed works must therefore be under=
taken by reference to the Policy definition of
 repair cost, and not by reference to a requirement to return repaired elem=
ents to their precise pre-loss condition or to an elevated aesthetic standa=
rd achieved through prior renovations.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">17. Where Tower el=
ects to manage the repairs, the works will be carried out with reasonable c=
are and skill and in compliance with applicable
 legal requirements. That obligation does not require the highest possible =
finish or the adoption of a particular trade standard unless expressly requ=
ired by the Policy or otherwise agreed.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ap=
tos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">18. Tower=E2=80=99=
s position remains that the proposed reinstatement works, when carried out =
in accordance with the agreed scope, will meet the Policy
 standard.</span><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family=
:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:=
p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-langu=
age:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
