ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Good aftern=
oon Lance,
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">I=E2=80=99v=
e just tried to call =E2=80=93 could you please call when convenient tomorr=
ow.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Unfortunate=
ly, your letter doesn=E2=80=99t address the specific concerns that Prendos =
has raised, or provide any consideration of the specific
 provisions which Tower says exempt all the work.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Apart from =
perhaps the floor joists mentioned at paragraph 4.a. of your letter, which =
are arguable / discretionary based on damage and
 interpretation, the rest of the works are specifically excluded from the e=
xemptions in Schedule 1. The general =E2=80=98maintenance=E2=80=99 provisio=
ns of schedule 1 item 1 do not override the specific exclusions in the rest=
 of the Schedule. Especially when all the work is
 being undertaken at once. Just one example is the internal load bearing an=
d bracing walls:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><img border=
=3D"0" width=3D"653" height=3D"177" style=3D"width:6.802in;height:1.8437in"=
 id=3D"_x0000_i1197" src=3D"cid:image027.jpg@01DCDEDC.6ACAA8B0"></span><spa=
n lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sa=
ns-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">I will happ=
ily talk you through the specific provisions of the Building Act schedule 1=
 if that would assist, but we do not accept that
 this work can be carried out without consent. If you have taken expert adv=
ice on this consenting, please provide it. Otherwise, please reconsider you=
r position.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
